 </p>

 <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
 <a href="/contact/" class="btn-primary text-base">
 Get a Quote
 <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"/></svg>
 </a>
 <a href="tel:+17029048923" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-2 py-3 font-mono text-sm font-medium tracking-wide text-white transition-colors hover:text-gold-400">
 <svg class="h-4 w-4 text-gold-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3 5a2 2 0 012-2h3.28a1 1 0 01.948.684l1.498 4.493a1 1 0 01-.502 1.21l-2.257 1.13a11.042 11.042 0 005.516 5.516l1.13-2.257a1 1 0 011.21-.502l4.493 1.498a1 1 0 01.684.949V19a2 2 0 01-2 2h-1C9.716 21 3 14.284 3 6V5z"/></svg>
 702.904.8923
 </a>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Local context — concrete -->
 <section class="bg-concrete py-20 sm:py-24">
 <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
 <div class="mb-12 max-w-2xl">
 <p class="kicker mb-3">Local Context</p>
 <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Summerlin is the <span class="text-gold-600">high-end build market.</span></h2>
 <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ash">
 Different game than Henderson tracts or NLV warehouses. Summerlin is custom-home estates, premium commercial fit-out, and master-plan execution. Cleaner uniforms, higher-end colorways, sharper foreman presentation.
 </p>
 </div>

 <div class="grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-3">
 {localContext.map((c) => (
 <div class="border border-hairline bg-panel p-7 transition-colors hover:border-gold-500">
 <span class="spec mb-4 inline-block border border-hairline px-2.5 py-1 text-gold-600">{c.code}</span>
 <h3 class="mb-3 font-heading text-xl font-bold uppercase leading-tight tracking-tight text-charcoal">{c.title}</h3>
 <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-ash">{c.body}</p>
 </div>
 ))}
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Trades we serve here — paper -->
 <section class="border-y border-hairline bg-paper py-20 sm:py-24">
 <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
 <div class="mb-12 max-w-2xl">
 <p class="kicker mb-3">The Trades</p>
 <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Trades we serve in <span class="text-gold-600">Summerlin.</span></h2>
 <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ash">
 The Summerlin mix leans residential-custom and commercial-fit-out. Service trades that work this end of the valley typically run a polo program for customer-facing techs and a branded-tee program for shop and warehouse.
 </p>
 </div>

 <div class="grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
 {trades.map((t) => (
 <a href={t.href} class="group flex flex-col border border-hairline bg-panel transition-colors hover:border-gold-500">
 <div class="aspect-[4/3] overflow-hidden">
 <img src={t.img} alt={t.name} class="h-full w-full object-cover transition-transform duration-500 group-hover:scale-105" loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="600" height="450" />
 </div>
 <div class="p-5">
 <h3 class="mb-2 font-heading text-lg font-bold uppercase tracking-tight text-charcoal group-hover:text-gold-600">{t.name}</h3>
 <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-ash">{t.detail}</p>
 </div>
 </a>
 ))}
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Typical orders — concrete -->
 <section class="bg-concrete py-20 sm:py-24">
 <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
 <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-16">
 <div>
 <p class="kicker mb-3">Typical Orders</p>
 <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">What we run for <span class="text-gold-600">Summerlin shops.</span></h2>
 <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ash">
 Smaller, sharper orders. Polos beat tees for anything customer-facing in this market. Most Summerlin clients run quarterly reorders with the spec already locked.
 </p>
 <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
 <a href="/services/" class="btn-secondary text-sm">All Services →</a>
 <a href="/company-stores/" class="btn-secondary text-sm">Company Stores →</a>
 </div>
 </div>

 <ul class="space-y-3">
 {useCases.map((u, i) => (
 <li class="flex items-start gap-4 border border-hairline bg-panel p-4 transition-colors hover:border-gold-500">
 <span class="shrink-0 font-mono text-xs font-bold text-gold-600">{String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}</span>
 <span class="text-base leading-relaxed text-charcoal">{u}</span>
 </li>
 ))}
 </ul>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Local context — paper -->
 <section class="border-y border-hairline bg-paper py-20 sm:py-24">
 <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
 <p class="kicker mb-3">Local Context</p>
 <h2 class="mb-8 font-heading text-3xl font-extrabold uppercase leading-tight tracking-tight text-charcoal sm:text-4xl">
 Custom branded apparel for Summerlin contractors, service trades, and HOA operations.
 </h2>

 <div class="space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ash">
 <p>
 Summerlin is one of the most demanding markets in the Vegas Valley for service-trade branding. The 22,500-acre master-planned community spans some of the highest-end residential addresses in Nevada — The Ridges, Red Rock Country Club, The Vistas, the Summerlin South villages — and the homeowners and HOAs in those communities expect service contractors to show up looking like an established professional business, not a side hustle in a t-shirt. Bighorn Threads delivers free to every Summerlin business address on qualifying orders, and we supply the embroidered polos, branded service uniforms, and professional-tier apparel that gets service trades repeat work in this market.
 </p>
 <p>
 For Summerlin landscape, irrigation, pool service, and pest control crews — the most-requested service trades in the community — the right uniform spec is an embroidered moisture-wicking polo with company logo on the left chest and (optionally) the technician's name on the right chest. Port Authority K540 Silk Touch Performance Polo and Cutter & Buck DryTec Performance are the two most-ordered SKUs for Summerlin service contractors because they look professional at a homeowner's front door and breathe well enough to handle a 110° afternoon route. Pants run khaki cargos or Carhartt B144 Rugged Flex shorts with embroidered logos on the back pocket for fleet visibility.
 </p>
 <p>
 For Summerlin residential general contractors and luxury home builders, the apparel spec leans premium. Custom-home GCs working in The Ridges or Red Rock Country Club send project managers and superintendents to client meetings expecting them to look the part — embroidered Cutter & Buck or Travis Mathew polos for client-facing roles, embroidered Eddie Bauer softshells for cold-weather walkthroughs, premium Carhartt for the field crew. We outfit Summerlin custom-home builders with full apparel programs that scale from solo-PM operations to 50-person commercial-quality residential firms.
 </p>
 <p>
 Summerlin HOA grounds-maintenance and community services contracts have specific branding requirements that differ from typical commercial landscape work. The HOAs frequently require the contractor's name, license number, and (sometimes) the HOA's preferred uniform color on field-crew apparel. We handle these multi-element decoration specs as a single coordinated embroidery program — left chest logo, sleeve-mounted license number, back-yoke contact info — all kept on file for the duration of the contract.
 </p>
 <p>
 We deliver to every Summerlin business address inside the Vegas Valley on qualifying orders. Drop direct to your office, your service truck staging area, or your active jobsite anywhere in Summerlin proper, Summerlin West, The Ridges, Red Rock Country Club, or any of the surrounding villages. Most Summerlin service-trade accounts run a company-store program with per-employee allowances and quarterly reorder cycles tied to seasonal work volume.
 </p>
 <p>
 Common requests in Summerlin: <a href="/blog/ansi-107-class-2-vs-class-3-hi-vis-las-vegas/" class="text-gold-600 underline decoration-gold-500/40 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-gold-500">Class 2 hi-vis</a>, <a href="/blog/rush-order-shirts-las-vegas-whats-possible/" class="text-gold-600 underline decoration-gold-500/40 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-gold-500">rush orders</a>, <a href="/blog/new-hire-workwear-checklist-las-vegas-contractors/" class="text-gold-600 underline decoration-gold-500/40 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-gold-500">new hire checklist</a>, and <a href="/industries/plumbing-hvac-las-vegas/" class="text-gold-600 underline decoration-gold-500/40 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-gold-500">plumbing &amp; HVAC service uniforms</a>.
 </p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- FAQs — concrete -->
 <section class="bg-concrete py-20 sm:py-24">
 <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
 <p class="kicker mb-3">FAQ</p>
 <h2 class="mb-12 font-heading text-3xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-charcoal sm:text-4xl">Questions Summerlin contractors ask us.</h2>

 <div class="divide-y divide-hairline border-y border-hairline">
 {faqs.map((f) => (
 <details class="group">
 <summary class="flex min-h-[56px] cursor-pointer list-none items-center justify-between gap-4 py-5 text-left">
 <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-bold uppercase leading-tight tracking-tight text-charcoal">{f.q}</h3>
 <svg class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-gold-600 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 4.5v15m7.5-7.5h-15"/></svg>
 </summary>
